Polly Walker Bio

Polly Walker is an accomplished actress from the United Kingdom. Born on May 19, 1966, in Warrington, England, Walker began her career in the film industry in the 1990s. Walker was raised in Scotland and later moved to London to pursue her career in the entertainment industry. Polly started her career in 1991, where she was featured in Derek Jarman's "Edward II." She also appeared in Paul W. S. Anderson's 1997 film "Event Horizon" and the 1998 film "Les Mis√©rables." Polly's breakthrough performance came in 2005 in the HBO series "Rome." She played Atia of the Julii, which earned her global recognition. Polly received a Saturn Award nomination for Best Supporting Actress in a Television Series for her outstanding performance in the series. Apart from her success in the film industry, Polly has also appeared in various television dramas. Some of her popular television appearances include her role as Faith in "Caprica," a spin-off to "Battlestar Galactica," and as Labia in "Deadwood." Additionally, Polly played the role of Lady Bexley in the ITV series "Mr. Selfridge" and Gillian Moon in "Line of Duty." Polly's remarkable career includes many prestigious film awards such as the Empire Award for Best Debut. She has also worked with some of the most recognized directors in the industry, including Ridley Scott, David Yates, and Martin Scorsese. Polly's talents as an actress have positioned her as one of the most iconic actresses in the United Kingdom. Her incredible performances on both the big and small screens have earned her a place among the most celebrated actors in the industry. Polly's accomplishments and contributions to the entertainment industry have solidified her position as one of the most successful actresses in the United Kingdom.
